  (* t t))

(define (ease-out-quad t)
  (- (* t (- 2 t))))

(define (draw)
  (let* ((t (/ (mod (millis) 2600) 2600.0))
         (x (+ 60 (* 280 (ease-in-quad t))))
         (y (+ 250 (* -140 (ease-out-quad t)))))
    (motion/clear)
    (motion/circle x y 10 \"fill\")))

(draw)
```

[VISUAL: A rising arc that accelerates horizontally and decelerates vertically, creating an asymmetric shape]

The horizontal motion starts slow and speeds up. The vertical motion starts fast and slows down. The arc has a unique character.

