### Arc with Trail

Drawing the last few positions to show the arc's shape.

```scheme
;; Arc with trailing positions
(define (draw)
  (let* ((base-t (/ (mod (millis) 2500) 2500.0)))
    (motion/clear)
    ;; Draw trail
    (let loop ((i 0))
      (when (< i 8)
        (let* ((offset (* i 0.03))
               (t (max 0 (- base-t offset)))
               (x (+ 60 (* t 280)))
               (y (+ 250 (* -140 (sin (* t 3.14159)))))
               (alpha (- 1.0 (* i 0.12))))
          (motion/circle x y 8 \"fill\"))
        (loop (+ i 1))))
    ;; Draw main dot
    (let* ((x (+ 60 (* base-t 280)))
           (y (+ 250 (* -140 (sin (* base-t 3.14159))))))
      (motion/circle x y 12 \"fill\"))))

(draw)
```

*[needs: opacity/alpha control for trail fade]*

[VISUAL: A dot with a fading trail of previous positions, revealing the arc's curve]

Each trailing position is offset in time. The loop draws them all.

