### Arc with Pause at the Peak

The motion slows to a stop at the highest point, then resumes.

```scheme
;; Pause at apex
(define (ease-pause-middle t)
  (cond
    ((< t 0.4) (* 2.5 t))
    ((< t 0.6) 1.0)
    (else (+ 1.0 (* 2.5 (- t 0.6))))))

(define (draw)
  (let* ((raw-t (/ (mod (millis) 3000) 3000.0))
         (t (min 2.0 (ease-pause-middle raw-t)))
         (t-clamped (min 1.0 t))
         (x (+ 60 (* t-clamped 280)))
         (y (+ 260 (* -150 (sin (* t-clamped 3.14159))))))
    (motion/clear)
    (motion/circle x y 11 \"fill\")))

(draw)
```

[VISUAL: The dot rises, holds at the peak for a moment, then descends]

The easing function maps the middle 20% of time to `t=1.0`, creating a pause.

