### Arc Derived from Velocity Vectors

Building position by integrating a velocity field.

```scheme
;; Position from velocity integration (Euler step)
(define (draw)
  (let* ((t (/ (mod (millis) 3000) 3000.0))
         (steps 30)
         (dt (/ t steps))
         (pos (let loop ((i 0) (x 60.0) (y 300.0))
                (if (>= i steps)
                    (list x y)
                    (let* ((vx 100)
                           (vy (- -200 (* 400 (/ i steps)))))
                      (loop (+ i 1)
                            (+ x (* vx dt))
                            (+ y (* vy dt))))))))
         (x (car pos))
         (y (cadr pos)))
    (motion/clear)
    (motion/circle x y 11 \"fill\")))

(draw)
```

*[needs: better numeric integration or pre-baked paths; Euler with 30 steps per frame is overkill]*

[VISUAL: A rising arc, position calculated by summing velocity over time]

This integrates velocity numerically to find position. It's more expensive than a closed-form equation.

