### Arc Following a Custom Easing Curve

Building an arc from a hand-tuned easing function.

```scheme
;; Custom easing for vertical motion
(define (ease-custom t)
  (cond
    ((< t 0.3) (* 3.33 t t))
    ((< t 0.7) (+ 0.33 (* 1.67 (- t 0.3))))
    (else (+ 1.0 (* -2.5 (- t 0.7) (- t 0.7))))))

(define (draw)
  (let* ((t (/ (mod (millis) 2600) 2600.0))
         (x (+ 60 (* t 280)))
         (y (+ 280 (* -160 (ease-custom t)))))
    (motion/clear)
    (motion/circle x y 10 \"fill\")))

(draw)
```

[VISUAL: An arc that accelerates, coasts, then settles with a slight dip]

The piecewise easing creates a non-standard arc shape.

