### Arc with Distance-Based Easing

Ease based on distance from the start point, not time.

```scheme
;; Distance-based easing (approximated via arc formula)
(define (ease-out-quad t)
  (- (* t (- 2 t))))

(define (draw)
  (let* ((t (/ (mod (millis) 2600) 2600.0))
         (x (+ 60 (* t 280)))
         (y-base (+ 250 (* -140 (sin (* t 3.14159)))))
         (dist (sqrt (+ (* (- x 60) (- x 60)) (* (- y-base 250) (- y-base 250)))))
         (max-dist 200)
         (ease-val (ease-out-quad (min 1.0 (/ dist max-dist))))
         (y (+ 250 (* -140 ease-val (sin (* t 3.14159))))))
    (motion/clear)
    (motion/circle x y 10 \"fill\")))

(draw)
```

*[needs: cleaner distance parameterization; this is a rough approximation]*

[VISUAL: An arc that rises more slowly at the start, based on accumulated distance]

Calculating true arc length in real time is expensive; this approximates it.

